# Personal job-hunt strategy notes (kept local, not for the public repo).
CAREER_ROADMAP.md

# Claude Code / AI authoring setup (LOCAL-ONLY, never committed).
# The agent pipeline and orchestration we use to *help build* DS-MSP are background
# tooling — not part of the library or its public docs. Keep them out entirely.
.claude/
# The doc-quality rubric the agents enforce names that pipeline, so it stays local too.
# (The public-facing writing standard is docs/WRITING_GUIDE.md.)
docs/research/doc_excellence_spec.md

# AI R&D process environment (LOCAL-ONLY, versioned in its OWN private git repo).
# `.ai/` holds the stage-gated R&D framework, the dedicated research/math/optimization
# agents+skills (canonical source), decision records, experiment logs, and upstream-
# codebase knowledge — the "how we drive the AI" layer. Kept out of the shared code repo
# so developers never see our AI-guided process or artifacts. Synced into .claude/ via
# `.ai/sync.sh`; the local CLAUDE.local.md orchestration pointer stays out too.
.ai/
CLAUDE.local.md

# Simulation / rendering studio (LOCAL-ONLY, never committed to this repo).
# It has its own local git repo and heavy viz dependencies (matplotlib, manim, …).
# RULE: the studio generates visual assets; only its OUTPUT (copied into assets/)
# lands here. The generator code and its deps stay out of GitHub entirely.
/simulations/

# Local detection/repro experiments (use datasets, not shipped).
/experiments/

# Internal calibration research reports (LOCAL-ONLY, never committed).
# Contains proprietary third-party camera-rig calibration data (vendor models,
# multi-sensor extrinsics) used to study model conversion. Keep out of GitHub.
/reports/
# Scratch diagnostics dropped in the repo root during investigations.
/diag_*.py
